comments.body:
@feedmeapples Thanks for the feedback. 

From your explanation looks like temporal has some private repo that the general public has no visibility of, so my question is how do people who are interested contributing to the project know which bug/fixes/features is currently worked on so that they can spend time investigating other things to avoid overlapping.

The CONTRIBUTING.md documentation does not explain anything that will help new contributors to get started and going directly without going through the maze of checking slack, etc. It would be beneficial if the process can be more clearer.
